Reasoning: The paper discusses the information theoretic aspects of molecular communication, which involves the transmission of information through molecules. This topic is highly interdisciplinary, involving biology, communication theory, and information theory. The paper specifically aims to bring molecular communication to the attention of information theorists, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the mathematical challenges of studying the capacity of molecular channels, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also reviews existing literature on the topic, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.BIO (Bioinformatics).
